data.chText: （有相同职业、爱好或信仰的）群体，同人；同好

data.hoverText: 可与单数或复数动词连用的可数名词

data.enText: a group of people sharing the same profession, interests or beliefs

data.chText: 医务界、银行界、赛马圈等同人
data.enText: members of the medical/banking/racing, etc. fraternity

data.chText: （美国男大学生的）联谊会， 兄弟会
data.enText: a club for a group of male students at an American college or university

data.chText: （团体内的）情谊，兄弟般友谊，博爱
data.enText: a feeling of friendship and support that exists between the members of a group

data.chText: 自由、平等和博爱的理想
data.enText: the ideals of liberty, equality and fraternity

simple_means.memory_skill: fratern 兄弟 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 兄弟情谊

means: (有相同职业、爱好或信仰的)群体

tr: people engaged in a particular occupation
a social club for male undergraduates

value.def: Fraternity refers to friendship and support between people who feel they are closely linked to each other.

example.ex: Bob needs the fraternity of others who share his mission.
example.tran: 鲍勃需要与他共同肩负这项使命的其他人的友爱互助。

value.def: You can refer to people who have the same profession or the same interests as a particular fraternity .

example.ex: ...the spread of stolen guns among the criminal fraternity.
example.tran: 盗窃枪支流入犯罪团伙手中

value.tran: 同业者;具有相同职业(或兴趣)的人

value.def: In the United States, a fraternity is a society of male university or college students.
value.tran: (美国男大学生)联谊会，兄弟会

partsOfSpeech.dec: fratern 兄弟 + al …的，具有…性质的 → 兄弟的；友善的
fratern 兄弟 + ity 具备某种性质，状况 → 兄弟情谊
